8   Totem runners partially implemented                              Medium

    Teams — BaseRunner: onMessage() handles respawn (0xF1 → Respawn
    UI event). No update(), no onRoster() override. Fine as-is only if
    the base never needs to broadcast or aggregate round-end data.

    Flag — FlagCompositeRunner: onMessage() covers BASE (respawn) and
    FLAG (state-change animations). No update(): the flag totem never
    broadcasts its own state periodically, which may be intentional but
    means players have no unsolicited flag-position feedback. No
    onRoster() override: flag totems send no capture summary at round end.

    Upkeep — UpkeepCompositeRunner: most complete. update() handles
    the full CP beacon / presence-window / scoring cycle. Still no
    onRoster() override; CP totems send no final-score contribution.

    All runners — onRoster() defaults to base (empty reply + Roster UI
    event). If totems should report per-device stats at game end
    (captures, CP ticks, etc.) this needs to be overridden per game.
